The paper discusses a machine learning optimization algorithm, specifically Bayesian optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves decision-making and optimization, which are topics covered in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of real and synthetic benchmarks, which suggests that the algorithm may fall under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, since the focus is on machine learning optimization, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories.
